 {"id": "bd-mn-1", "title": "PORT: mntent sub-bead 1 \u2014 core::mntent pure-safe parser/serializer", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "task", "epic": "bd-mn-epic", "created_at": "2026-04-24T09:27:47.180840Z", "description": "Add crates/frankenlibc-core/src/mntent/mod.rs with: MntFields<a> (six byte-slice field references), parse_mntent_line(line) -> Option<MntFields> handling blank/comment lines, freq/passno default-zero parsing, has_mnt_opt(opts, opt) -> Option<usize> scanning comma-separated tokens, and format_mntent_line(fields, out: &mut Vec<u8>) producing fstab-style \"fsname dir type opts freq passno\n\". All operate on &[u8]; no allocation in parsers; tests cover blank/comment skip, partial fields, leading/trailing whitespace, options with embedded commas as separators, edge-case option matching at start/end of string."}
 {"id": "bd-mn-2", "title": "PORT: mntent sub-bead 2 \u2014 rewire abi shims to core", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "task", "epic": "bd-mn-epic", "created_at": "2026-04-24T09:27:47.180840Z", "description": "Refactor unistd_abi.rs hasmntopt, getmntent_r, addmntent to delegate to core::mntent::{has_mnt_opt, parse_mntent_line, format_mntent_line}. Keep the C-ABI marshalling (mntent struct field pointers, caller buffer packing, BufReader/Write integration) at the boundary. Verify any conformance_diff_mntent tests still pass."}
 {"id": "bd-mn-1", "title": "PORT: mntent sub-bead 1 \u2014 core::mntent pure-safe parser/serializer", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "task", "epic": "bd-mn-epic", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T09:29:33.308150Z", "resolution": "Added crates/frankenlibc-core/src/mntent/{mod.rs,parse.rs} with: borrowed MntFields<a> (six byte-slice field references), parse_mntent_line() (handles blank/comment lines, EOL stripping, runs of whitespace, default-zero freq/passno fallback), has_mnt_opt() (token-aware comma-separated option scan), parse_mntent_freq_passno() (i32 with garbage-fallback), and format_mntent_line() (in-place i32-to-decimal serialization including i32::MIN). 26 unit tests cover blank/comment skip, partial fields, leading whitespace, run-collapse, embedded-token boundary cases (substring guard), key=value option matching, round-trip identity, and a real /proc/mounts line."}
+{"id": "bd-mn-2", "title": "PORT: mntent sub-bead 2 \u2014 rewire abi shims to core", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "task", "epic": "bd-mn-epic", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T09:31:32.159525Z", "resolution": "Refactored frankenlibc-abi/src/unistd_abi.rs hasmntopt (was ~12 lines of inline window/comma scan), getmntent_r (was ~85 lines of inline parser + 4x copy_nonoverlapping NUL packing), and addmntent (was ~15 lines of CStr->String->format!). All three now delegate to frankenlibc_core::mntent::{has_mnt_opt, parse_mntent_line, format_mntent_line}. The C-ABI marshalling \u2014 mntent struct field-pointer writes, caller-buffer NUL packing via a closure, BufReader/Write integration \u2014 stays at the boundary. Verified: 2/2 mntent unistd_abi tests pass, 178/178 unistd_abi tests pass overall."}
+{"id": "bd-mn-epic", "title": "PORT: mntent (fstab/mtab) family native Rust impl", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "epic", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T09:31:32.159525Z", "resolution": "Epic complete in 2 sub-beads. bd-mn-1: core::mntent module (parse_mntent_line, has_mnt_opt, format_mntent_line, parse_mntent_freq_passno) with 26 unit tests. bd-mn-2: abi shims rewired. Net effect: ~110 lines of inline parsing + manual NUL packing in unistd_abi.rs replaced by ~50 lines of marshalling over a pure-safe Rust module that lives inside #![deny(unsafe_code)]. The line parser is now reachable from any caller (not just getmntent_r) and exhaustively tested in isolation."}

